# Task Manager - Git Ignore File
# Excludes sensitive information and generated files

# ==========================================
# SENSITIVE INFORMATION - DO NOT COMMIT
# ==========================================

# Calendar sync URL (contains private calendar token)
.calendar_sync_url

# Downloaded calendar files (may contain private events)
calendar.ics
calendar_backup.md

# Email folder - contains confidential communications
emails/

# Current work folder - contains work-in-progress and potentially sensitive documents
current-work/

# Notes folder - contains meeting notes, PDFs, and sensitive documents
notes/

# Data exports (may contain private info)
Coursera\ Courses/**/*.csv
Coursera\ Courses/**/*.xlsx
Coursera\ Courses/**/*.json

# Any credentials or API keys
*.key
*.pem
*.p12
**/credentials.json
**/secrets.json
# Environment config (but keep the example)
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# ==========================================
# GENERATED FILES
# ==========================================

# Python cache
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.Python
*.so
.ruff_cache/

# Generated HTML files (can be regenerated)
deadline_dashboard.html
current-work/*.html
emails/drafts/*.html

# OS files
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db

# Editor files
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.vscode/
.idea/

# Temporary files
*.tmp
*.temp
*.log

# ==========================================
# KEEP THESE FILES (exceptions)
# ==========================================

# Keep README files
!emails/README.md
!current-work/README.md
!README.md

# Keep documentation
!QUICK_REFERENCE.md

# Keep the meeting agenda markdown (source files)
!current-work/*_Meeting_Agenda_*.md

# ==========================================
# NOTES
# ==========================================

# This gitignore protects:
# 1. Private calendar URLs and calendar data
# 2. Email PDFs and attachments with confidential info
# 3. Work documents (Excel, Word, PDF) that may contain sensitive data
# 4. Credentials, API keys, and secrets
# 5. Generated files that can be recreated

# What gets committed:
# - Source code (Python scripts)
# - Documentation (README, markdown guides)
# - Task structure (data/tasks.json without sensitive details)
# - Calendar structure (data/calendar.json can be committed if you remove private events)
# - Scripts and automation tools
